725982f-a.title: Queens: 168th Street - Jamaica Avenue
725982f-a.text:
92-86 - 168th Street, west side, between the Long lIsland Railroad tracks and Jamaica Ave., showing the Amos Denton house.
In 1931 a one story garage occupied the site.
January 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726988f-b.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - 168th Street
726988f-b.text:
Jamaica Ave., south side, between 168th Street and 168th Place, showing in a set of three views the JJohn Graoyhouse of 1873. It was till the estate's property in 1891. If standing in 1931, it would stand on lots 10 to 12 in block 1171. Demolition of this house which
is said to be 100 years old began on July 1, 1925.
1922.
View 2: May 1923.
View 3: February 8, 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

725970f-a.title: Queens: 168th Street - Jamaica Avenue
725970f-a.text:
168th Street, west side, between the Log Island Railroad tracks and Jamaica Ave., showing Mrs. Hewlett's house of 1873. In 1891 it was a part of the S.T. Wooley Estate. In 1931 a three
